<h1 id='authentication'>Authentication</h1>
<blockquote>
<p>To get an access token, send the following request:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code>curl --insecure --user <span class="s1">'clientid:clientsecret'</span> <span class="s1">'https://go.screver.com/oauth/token'</span> --data <span class="s1">'grant_type=client_credentials'</span>
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>Make sure to replace <code>clientid</code> and <code>clientsecret</code> with your OAuth client id and secret.</p>

<p>The above command returns structure like this:</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight http tab-http"><code><span class="k">HTTP</span><span class="o">/</span><span class="m">1.1</span> <span class="m">200</span> <span class="ne">OK</span>
<span class="na">Content-Type</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="s">application/json</span>
</code></pre><pre class="highlight json tab-json"><code><span class="p">{</span><span class="w">
  </span><span class="s2">"token_type"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="s2">"Bearer"</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w">
  </span><span class="s2">"access_token"</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="s2">"u8ptxAd2hJ3aRjtgwwmUqqkNpcMOYxf3"</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="p">}</span><span class="w">
</span></code></pre>
<p>To allow access to the API use access token.
An OAuth client credentials request is used to obtain a token.
To get your OAuth <code>client id</code> and <code>client secret</code> please contact us.
The token can be used 24h.</p>

<p><code>Authorization: Bearer u8ptxAd2hJ3aRjtgwwmUqqkNpcMOYxf3</code></p>

<aside class="notice">
You must replace <code>u8ptxAd2hJ3aRjtgwwmUqqkNpcMOYxf3</code> with the access token you received from the OAuth request.
</aside>
